# .pii-patterns — LOCAL, gitignored denylist for the pre-commit pii-guard.
#
# One POSIX extended-regex (ERE) per line, matched case-insensitively against
# staged ADDED lines. Blank lines and #-comments are ignored.
#
# Keep the real file LOCAL — never commit it; the actual terms are the PII.
# `make hooks-install` copies this template to .pii-patterns and appends your
# git identity (name + email) so commits are protected out of the box.
#
# Add your real dev-data terms below. Examples (commented — adapt, don't ship):
#   Jane Doe
#   jane\.doe@example\.com
#   [0-9]{4}[ -]?[0-9]{4}[ -]?[0-9]{4}    # an account-number shape you use
#   PT [A-Z][a-z]+ Makmur                 # a real entity / employer name
